            <attribute conformance="R" isMandatory="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="name" sortKey="6">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p>The patient's requested new name.</p>
                            <p>Where the particular flavour of the person name dataType used here is Person name structured (number 5 in the dataTypes description list).    The name contains the following components from this flavour of the dataType: </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>A <i>family </i>element to carry the surname or family name of the person (mandatory) </li>
                            </ul>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Up to 2 <i>given </i>elements to carry the given names of the person. If the person has more than 2 given names, these will be concatenated in the second given name attribute with a space between each name. The order of the elements is also significant, so the first occurrence of the <i>given </i>element will carry the first given name, and the second occurrence will carry the second, third, etc. given names (mandatory) </li>
                            </ul>
                            <ul>
                                <li>A <i>prefix </i>element to carry a prefix for the name, such as Mr, Mrs, etc. (mandatory)  <br/>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </text>
                    </otherAnnotation>
                </annotations>
                <derivationSupplier attributeName="name"
                    className="Person" staticModelDerivationId="1"/>
                <type name="PN"/>
            </attribute>
            <attribute conformance="R" isMandatory="true"
                maximumMultiplicity="1" minimumMultiplicity="1"
                name="administrativeGenderCode" sortKey="1">
                <annotations>
                    <otherAnnotation type="html">
                        <text>
                            <p>The administrative gender of the person.  </p>
                            <p>The Coded Only datatype flavour is used to carry this information as follows:      </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>The <i>code </i>attribute will contain a value from the list of codes in the <u>Sex</u> vocabulary. </li>
                            </ul>
                        </text>
